  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">School Sanitation Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provide water well to begin project. Construction of pit latrine for school, as first stage of pilot project. WFSS will conduct further monitoring to assess school&apos;s maintenance of latrine. Successful maintenance will be required to enable second stage of additional latrines to serve all students.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water for South Sudan (WFSS) has been drilling water wells in South Sudan since 2005, and providing hygiene education since 2014.

In 2015 WFSS began researching sanitation projects, and spent two years gathering information, and assessing possible locations for a pilot sanitation project.

In 2017 Zogolona Primary School in Wau was chosen as the site to inaugurate our sanitation services. Zogolona serves approximately 800 students. The school and community demonstrated their willingness to meet all criteria for maintaining a pit latrine.</narrative>
  </description>
